 1/7/18 Matthew and Dunda left today for England . At 10.30 with Stewart set out again for the line and this time went over the same ground as yesterday save that we kept out of the villag . Went up to Digger Support past the usual bivouac of the men and had a look round . Not much could be seen from the right but on the left we could see Vair Wood , sundri direlict aeroplan and a doubl telegraph post which are good landmark . Some fine shell of our were burst on the Hun trench in a wealth of thick wooli smoke and dust . Return with Colonel Forb who happen to also be up and came back to fire line B.H.Q . Just as we arriv Fritz put over a coupl of salvo of big one which
